dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: A dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in computer vision tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: A dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 different classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for training machine learning models in more complex image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Ilya Sutskever
Geoffrey E Hinton
dcterms:description: A large-scale dataset containing over 14 million images labeled across 1,000 categories, widely used for training deep learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: ImageNet
